matter, that you have yourself to care for before the rest of the world. that it's okay to have been hurt, it doesn't make you damaged and if it does that's alright too. i think our relationship makes me realise wrong timing is bullshit, that you can be at your lowest low

we've promised our past selves. 

you owe yourself kindness.

i suppose she would only laugh and say that's silly. that there's no point to such erasure. that the hurt is a part of you, the past a settled  sediment in the mixture that is the present. so i tell myself all i can do is cherish her, and myself, and remind each other of the love

kshi is not as strong as she seems, not as perpetually happy, and definitely not as unscathed as she'll have you believe. she admits vulnerability very rarely and when she does it feels like my heart has been broken into a million pieces. i wish i could erase the past hurt.

responsible for being abandoned, mistreated, scarred and taken advantage of. she admitted to the same, sometimes in quietly fierce ways that made it seem like she had come to a resolution about the past- that they weren't going to keep defining her. i was jealous and in awe.
